comment: Lemma for ~ heibor . Since the sequence of balls connected by the function ` T ` ensures that each ball nontrivially intersects with the next (since the empty set has a finite subcover, the intersection of any two successive balls in the sequence is nonempty), and each ball is half the size of the previous one, the distance between the centers is at most ` 3 / 2 ` times the size of the larger, and so if we expand each ball by a factor of ` 3 ` we get a nested sequence of balls. (Contributed by Jeff Madsen, 23-Jan-2014.)
